id: pm-t4wb
title: Telemetry schema versioning/negotiation preparation
description: TELEMETRY_SCHEMA_VERSION=1 is hardcoded and stamped on every event with no documented upgrade protocol; becomes a reliability risk if the event structure must change.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:observability","area:telemetry",living-map,reliability
created_at: "2026-05-31T19:45:03.489Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-06T05:04:59.435Z"
author: maintainer-agent
acceptance_criteria: ADR documents the negotiation protocol; queue entries carry client_schema_version distinct from event schema_version; endpoint probe parses an advertised server max-version header; tests assert schema_version on all 3 event types; no v1 behavior change.
value: TELEMETRY_SCHEMA_VERSION=1 is hardcoded and stamped on every event with no documented upgrade protocol; becomes a reliability risk if the event structure must change.
parent: pm-5oj5
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-06T04:45:11.363Z",codex-telemetry-batch,"Kickoff: implementing telemetry schema negotiation preparation with backward-compatible queue metadata, health endpoint version negotiation parsing, ADR docs, and regression tests in one bundled PR with pm-6xdl."
  "2026-06-06T05:04:53.197Z",codex-telemetry-batch,"Implemented telemetry schema negotiation prep with backward compatibility: queue envelope now writes client_schema_version=1 while each event payload keeps schema_version=1; health endpoint probe now parses advertised server max schema version headers (x-pm-telemetry-max-schema-version and x-pm-telemetry-max-version) and exposes endpoint_probe.max_schema_version in telemetry details; runtime classification marks telemetry command as diagnostics and telemetry clear instrumentation is skipped so clear does not recreate queue files. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts tests/unit/health-command.spec.ts, node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (100% lines/branches/functions/statements), and full gates pnpm build && pnpm typecheck && pnpm contracts:check && pnpm quality:static && pnpm security:scan && pnpm audit --audit-level low all passed."
